# Markdown formatting

When writing or editing `.md` files in this project:

- **Do not wrap prose at 80–100 characters.** Write each sentence or logical thought as a single continuous line. Let the editor wrap visually.
- Tables, code blocks, and YAML/list items are exempt — those keep natural line breaks.
- This applies to all docs: runbooks, DDDs, NOTES.md, README files, etc.

## Example

❌ BAD — hard-wrapped prose:
```
The k3s agent uses an internal load balancer proxy on 127.0.0.1:6444.
All agent traffic goes through this proxy first. The proxy dials the
real cluster endpoint. If the proxy can't reach the cluster, it resets
incoming connections.
```

✅ GOOD — continuous lines:
```
The k3s agent uses an internal load balancer proxy on 127.0.0.1:6444. All agent traffic goes through this proxy first. The proxy dials the real cluster endpoint. If the proxy can't reach the cluster, it resets incoming connections — producing the misleading `connection reset by peer` on `127.0.0.1:6444`.
```
